Nigeria’s COVID-19 second wave continued to rise as indicated on Wednesday night as 1,016 new confirmed cases were reported across the country, taking Nigeria’s total to 86,576. According to the latest update by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) gathered from 20 states and Federal Capital Territory (FCT) and made available via its verified Twitter handle, @NCDCgov, Lagos reported the highest number of new cases with 434 infections. On the list of the top five states with the highest number of new infections for the day shows that FCT recorded 155 cases to place second, Plateau – 94 in third place, Kaduna and Rivers, with 56 new infections, are in joint fourth place. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The update also reveals that 1,385 persons were discharged today after for the day after they recovered from the virus, bringing the total number of recoveries to 73,322. Eleven deaths were also recorded from across the country, taking the death toll from COVID-19 in Nigeria to 1,278 since the February 27 index cases was discovered in Lagos. Real Madrid Draw At Elche, Lose Chance To Close Gap On Laliga Leaders Atletico EU Leaders Formally Sign Post-Brexit UK Trade Deal The breakdown of the latest update is as follows: Lagos-434 FCT-155 Plateau-94 Kaduna-56 Rivers-56 Oyo-30 Nasarawa-27 Zamfara-25 Abia-22 Enugu-18 Kano-18 Bayelsa-15 Edo-14 Ogun-11 Borno-10 Ebonyi-10 Jigawa-7 Anambra-4 Delta-3 Niger-3 Osun-3 86,576 confirmed 73,322 discharged 1,278 deaths SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION